<p data-start="253" data-end="281">A few notes before the text:</p>
<ul data-start="283" data-end="753">
<li data-start="283" data-end="388">
<p data-start="285" data-end="388">I will use <strong data-start="296" data-end="333"><code data-start="298" data-end="308">biblatex</code> with author–year style</strong>, since that fits <em data-start="351" data-end="375">AI / CogSci / Synthese</em> venues best.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="389" data-end="452">
<p data-start="391" data-end="452">Citations are <strong data-start="405" data-end="427">conceptual anchors</strong>, not exhaustive surveys.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="453" data-end="580">
<p data-start="455" data-end="580">Where there are multiple possible citations (e.g. coherence, basal cognition), I select the <em data-start="547" data-end="574">strongest, most canonical</em> ones.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="581" data-end="655">
<p data-start="583" data-end="655">I will include a <strong data-start="600" data-end="625">complete bibliography</strong> at the end, ready to compile.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="656" data-end="753">
<p data-start="658" data-end="753">This is written to survive a <strong data-start="687" data-end="714">serious theory reviewer</strong>, not just be “related work compliant.”</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="755" data-end="829">Below is the <strong data-start="768" data-end="784">entire paper</strong>, clean LaTeX, no Markdown, ready to compile.</p>
