<p data-start="6152" data-end="6193">That last clause matters philosophically.</p>
<hr data-start="6195" data-end="6198">
<h2 data-start="6200" data-end="6238">3. Net Effect (Reviewer Psychology)</h2>
<p data-start="6240" data-end="6296">After these edits, reviewers will perceive the paper as:</p>
<ul data-start="6298" data-end="6410">
<li data-start="6298" data-end="6328">
<p data-start="6300" data-end="6328"><strong data-start="6300" data-end="6316">More precise</strong>, not longer</p>
</li>
<li data-start="6329" data-end="6368">
<p data-start="6331" data-end="6368"><strong data-start="6331" data-end="6350">Better grounded</strong>, not more applied</p>
</li>
<li data-start="6369" data-end="6410">
<p data-start="6371" data-end="6410"><strong data-start="6371" data-end="6397">Conceptually confident</strong>, not evasive</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="6412" data-end="6422">Crucially:</p>
<ul data-start="6423" data-end="6570">
<li data-start="6423" data-end="6468">
<p data-start="6425" data-end="6468">You avoid the “hand-wavy theory” critique</p>
</li>
<li data-start="6469" data-end="6520">
<p data-start="6471" data-end="6520">You avoid the “where are the experiments?” trap</p>
</li>
<li data-start="6521" data-end="6570">
<p data-start="6523" data-end="6570">You keep EAIMR <em data-start="6538" data-end="6547">general</em>, not benchmark-bound</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="6572" data-end="6661">This is exactly how strong theoretical frameworks survive first contact with peer review.</p>
<p data-start="6663" data-end="6687">If you want, next I can:</p>
<ul data-start="6688" data-end="6861">
<li data-start="6688" data-end="6751">
<p data-start="6690" data-end="6751">apply <em data-start="6696" data-end="6701">all</em> these micro-edits into a single clean LaTeX diff,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="6752" data-end="6861">
<p data-start="6754" data-end="6861">or help you do a <strong data-start="6771" data-end="6802">journal-specific final pass</strong> (e.g. Cognitive Science vs. Artificial Intelligence tone).</p>
</li>
</ul>
