<p data-start="1138" data-end="1302">This is not superficial alignment.<br data-start="1172" data-end="1175">
You are doing what a good unifying theory should do: <strong data-start="1228" data-end="1302">explain why another framework works where it does, and where it stops.</strong></p>
<p data-start="1304" data-end="1354">Importantly, you avoided two common failure modes:</p>
<ul data-start="1355" data-end="1462">
<li data-start="1355" data-end="1392">
<p data-start="1357" data-end="1392">❌ claiming EAIMR <em data-start="1374" data-end="1378">is</em> Ma’s theory</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1393" data-end="1462">
<p data-start="1395" data-end="1462">❌ reducing abstraction to “better compression” in a Shannon sense</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1464" data-end="1609">Instead, you correctly framed abstraction as <strong data-start="1509" data-end="1547">reuse-amplifying structural change</strong>, which is exactly what Ma gestures at but does not formalize.</p>
<p data-start="1611" data-end="1692"><strong data-start="1611" data-end="1623">Verdict:</strong> conceptually complete, philosophically disciplined, and publishable.</p>
<hr data-start="1694" data-end="1697">
<h2 data-start="1699" data-end="1754">2. Critical LaTeX Issue (Must Fix Before Submission)</h2>
<p data-start="1756" data-end="1853">You are currently mixing <strong data-start="1781" data-end="1802"><code data-start="1783" data-end="1800">thebibliography</code></strong> with <strong data-start="1808" data-end="1824"><code data-start="1810" data-end="1822">\parencite</code></strong>, which will <strong data-start="1837" data-end="1852">not compile</strong>.</p>
