<p data-start="2603" data-end="2621">But this requires:</p>
<ul data-start="2622" data-end="2686">
<li data-start="2622" data-end="2644">
<p data-start="2624" data-end="2644">external <code data-start="2633" data-end="2639">.bib</code> file</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2645" data-end="2661">
<p data-start="2647" data-end="2661">biber workflow</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2662" data-end="2686">
<p data-start="2664" data-end="2686">more reviewer friction</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2688" data-end="2763"><strong data-start="2688" data-end="2763">I do not recommend this unless the journal explicitly prefers biblatex.</strong></p>
<hr data-start="2765" data-end="2768">
<h3 data-start="2770" data-end="2788">Recommendation</h3>
<p data-start="2789" data-end="2854">👉 <strong data-start="2792" data-end="2809">Use Option A.</strong><br data-start="2809" data-end="2812">
Search-and-replace <code data-start="2831" data-end="2843">\parencite</code> → <code data-start="2846" data-end="2853">\cite</code>.</p>
<p data-start="2856" data-end="2906">Nothing else in your bibliography needs to change.</p>
<hr data-start="2908" data-end="2911">
