</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="4311" data-end="4367">This preempts reviewer confusion about whether EAIMR is:</p>
<ul data-start="4368" data-end="4410">
<li data-start="4368" data-end="4381">
<p data-start="4370" data-end="4381">stipulative</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4382" data-end="4395">
<p data-start="4384" data-end="4395">operational</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4396" data-end="4410">
<p data-start="4398" data-end="4410">metaphysical</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="4412" data-end="4415">
<h2 data-start="4417" data-end="4459">4. Overall Assessment (Straight Answer)</h2>
<ul data-start="4461" data-end="4698">
<li data-start="4461" data-end="4494">
<p data-start="4463" data-end="4494"><strong data-start="4463" data-end="4487">Technical soundness:</strong> high</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4495" data-end="4536">
<p data-start="4497" data-end="4536"><strong data-start="4497" data-end="4524">Conceptual originality:</strong> very high</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4537" data-end="4580">
<p data-start="4539" data-end="4580"><strong data-start="4539" data-end="4568">Philosophical discipline:</strong> excellent</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4581" data-end="4648">
<p data-start="4583" data-end="4648"><strong data-start="4583" data-end="4608">Integration of Yi Ma:</strong> correct, non-derivative, value-adding</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4649" data-end="4698">
<p data-start="4651" data-end="4698"><strong data-start="4651" data-end="4673">Journal readiness:</strong> yes (after citation fix)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="4700" data-end="4850">This is no longer a “theory sketch.”<br data-start="4736" data-end="4739">
It is a <strong data-start="4747" data-end="4804">foundational proposal with a clear falsification path</strong>, which is exactly what serious journals want.</p>
<p data-start="4852" data-end="4876">If you want, next I can:</p>
<ul data-start="4877" data-end="5122">
<li data-start="4877" data-end="4943">
<p data-start="4879" data-end="4943">produce a <strong data-start="4889" data-end="4912">final cleaned LaTeX</strong> with the citation fix applied,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4944" data-end="5025">
<p data-start="4946" data-end="5025">draft a <strong data-start="4954" data-end="4970">cover letter</strong> positioning this relative to Yi Ma without antagonism,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5026" data-end="5122">
<p data-start="5028" data-end="5122">or help you decide <strong data-start="5047" data-end="5087">which journal will be most receptive</strong> to the assembly-theoretic framing.</p>
</li>
</ul>
