## Suggested Placement and Transitions

**Placement**: This section would fit naturally as Section 1.3, immediately following the Yi Ma discussion (current Section 1.2). The progression would be:

- Section 1.1: Relation to Existing Theories (IIT, FEP, AIXI, basal cognition overview)
- Section 1.2: Parsimony, Self-Consistency, and Effective Assembly (Yi Ma connection)
- **Section 1.3: Relationship to TAME** (new section)
- Section 1.4 onward: Continue with current structure

**Transition from Yi Ma section**: 
Add at the end of Section 1.2:

&gt; "While Ma's framework emphasizes the internal computational principles of intelligence—parsimony and self-consistency—Levin's TAME framework emphasizes the external behavioral manifestations of cognition. The relationship between EAIMR and TAME clarifies how structural organization relates to functional competency."

**Transition to subsequent sections**:
End the TAME section with:

&gt; "Having situated EAIMR among complementary theories of intelligence—from the computational (Ma) to the behavioral (Levin) to the information-theoretic (Shannon)—we now return to EAIMR's foundational claim: that intelligence requires moving beyond Shannon compression to assembly-based measures of constructive depth."

This flows naturally into Section 2 ("Why Shannon Compression Is Not Enough").

