 @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(6)] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(16)] px-(--thread-content-margin)"><div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn" tabindex="-1"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col grow"><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="c0ec99c7-55c0-46ea-a102-4581b00118ad" dir="auto" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-2"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="259">Great instinct. You’re right that this section can be <strong data-start="54" data-end="106">shortened, sharpened, and made more mathematical</strong>, and doing so actually <em data-start="130" data-end="143">strengthens</em> the paper by tying TAME, Ma, and EAIMR together at the level of <strong data-start="208" data-end="229">semantic geometry</strong> rather than prose comparison.</p>
<p data-start="261" data-end="324">Below is a <strong data-start="272" data-end="295">replacement version</strong> of the TAME section that is:</p>
<ul data-start="326" data-end="588">
<li data-start="326" data-end="345">
<p data-start="328" data-end="345">~40–45% shorter</p>
</li>
<li data-start="346" data-end="373">
<p data-start="348" data-end="373">Explicitly mathematical</p>
</li>
<li data-start="374" data-end="439">
<p data-start="376" data-end="439">Introduces <strong data-start="387" data-end="439">summarization vs extension as the same operation</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="440" data-end="489">
<p data-start="442" data-end="489">Frames both as <strong data-start="457" data-end="489">flows on a semantic manifold</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="490" data-end="539">
<p data-start="492" data-end="539">Uses <strong data-start="497" data-end="514">KL divergence</strong> as the unifying quantity</p>
</li>
<li data-start="540" data-end="588">
<p data-start="542" data-end="588">Keeps TAME, Ma, and EAIMR cleanly integrated</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="590" data-end="672">You can drop this in as <strong data-start="614" data-end="629">Section 1.3</strong>, replacing the longer prose-heavy version.</p>
